OL,3,CThe self-made tycoon now dubbed a
OL,4,C'monster': Who was Mohamed Al Fayed?
OL,6,FIn the 1980s, he hit the headlines as
OL,7,Fhe battled for control of the House of
OL,8,FFraser group, including its flagship
OL,9,Fstore Harrods, with rival tycoon
OL,10,FRoland "Tiny" Rowland.
OL,12,FAl Fayed and his brother bought a 30%
OL,13,Fstake in House Of Fraser from Mr
OL,14,FRowland in 1984, and took control of
OL,15,FHarrods for #615 million the following
OL,16,Fyear.
OL,18,FMr Rowland's London and Rhodesian
OL,19,FMining Company (Lonrho) had attempted
OL,20,Fto buy Harrods but was beaten to it by
OL,21,Fthe Egyptian family.
