OL,3,CThe self-made tycoon now dubbed a
OL,4,C'monster': Who was Mohamed Al Fayed?
OL,6,FMr Rowland later accused Mr Al Fayed
OL,7,Fof breaking into his safety deposit
OL,8,Fbox at the department store.
OL,10,FThe Egyptian-born was arrested in
OL,11,FMarch 1998 along with Harrods security
OL,12,Fdirector John Macnamara and four other
OL,13,Fstore staff, but was never charged. In
OL,14,F2000, Mohamed Al Fayed agreed to pay
OL,15,Fthe widow of Tiny Rowland more than
OL,16,F#1.4m for gemstones "stolen" from Mr
OL,17,FRowland's safety deposit box.
OL,19,FAl Fayed later expanded his business
OL,20,Finterests to include the Paris Ritz
OL,21,Fand Fulham Football Club.
